#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:5
msgid "How to Add \"Remember Me\" Login Functionality"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:7
msgid ""
"Once a user is authenticated, their credentials are typically stored in "
"the session. This means that when the session ends they will be logged "
"out and have to provide their login details again next time they wish to "
"access the application. You can allow users to choose to stay logged in "
"for longer than the session lasts using a cookie with the ``remember_me``"
" firewall option:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:85
msgid "The ``remember_me`` firewall defines the following configuration options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:89
msgid "``secret`` (**required**)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:88
msgid ""
"The value used to encrypt the cookie's content. It's common to use the "
"``secret`` value defined in the ``APP_SECRET`` environment variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:95
msgid "``name`` (default value: ``REMEMBERME``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:92
msgid ""
"The name of the cookie used to keep the user logged in. If you enable the"
" ``remember_me`` feature in several firewalls of the same application, "
"make sure to choose a different name for the cookie of each firewall. "
"Otherwise, you'll face lots of security related problems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:99
msgid "``lifetime`` (default value: ``31536000``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:98
msgid ""
"The number of seconds during which the user will remain logged in. By "
"default users are logged in for one year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:104
msgid "``path`` (default value: ``/``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:102
msgid ""
"The path where the cookie associated with this feature is used. By "
"default the cookie will be applied to the entire website but you can "
"restrict to a specific section (e.g. ``/forum``, ``/admin``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:108
msgid "``domain`` (default value: ``null``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:107
msgid ""
"The domain where the cookie associated with this feature is used. By "
"default cookies use the current domain obtained from ``$_SERVER``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:112
msgid "``secure`` (default value: ``false``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:111
msgid ""
"If ``true``, the cookie associated with this feature is sent to the user "
"through an HTTPS secure connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:117
msgid "``httponly`` (default value: ``true``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:115
msgid ""
"If ``true``, the cookie associated with this feature is accessible only "
"through the HTTP protocol. This means that the cookie won't be accessible"
" by scripting languages, such as JavaScript."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:121
msgid "``samesite`` (default value: ``null``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:120
msgid ""
"If set to ``strict``, the cookie associated with this feature will not be"
" sent along with cross-site requests, even when following a regular link."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:126
msgid "``remember_me_parameter`` (default value: ``_remember_me``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:124
msgid ""
"The name of the form field checked to decide if the \"Remember Me\" "
"feature should be enabled or not. Keep reading this article to know how "
"to enable this feature conditionally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:131
msgid "``always_remember_me`` (default value: ``false``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:129
msgid ""
"If ``true``, the value of the ``remember_me_parameter`` is ignored and "
"the \"Remember Me\" feature is always enabled, regardless of the desire "
"of the end user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:135
msgid "``token_provider`` (default value: ``null``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:134
msgid ""
"Defines the service id of a token provider to use. If you want to store "
"tokens in the database, see :ref:`remember-me-token-in-database`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:143
msgid "``service`` (default value: ``null``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:138
msgid ""
"Defines the ID of the service used to handle the Remember Me feature. "
"It's useful if you need to overwrite the current behavior entirely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/remember_me.rst:143
msgid "The ``service`` option was introduced in Symfony 5.1."
msgstr ""

